condition.narrative: Section I.A.1, I.B.1 and I.C.1: The Recipient shall take all necessary measures, or cause others to take such measures, to ensureimplementation of the Project is in accordance with the provisions of the National Project Report, which includes, among others,Financial Management Manual, Procurement Manual, Governance and Accountability Acton Plan (GAAP), Environmental and SocialManagement Plan (ESMP).

Section I.A.10: The Recipient shall ensure that each participating Project States will maintain dedicated, multi-disciplinary teamof suitably qualified personnel in each Pilot Investment Execution Agency (PEA) with resources sufficient to carry out theirrespective part of the Project under Components two, three and four

Section I.A.4: The Recipient, through NPMU, will cause each Project State to: (a) make such annual budgetary allocations as shallbe required to pay for ten percent (10%) of the estimated cost of implementing its Respective Part of the Project, and transfersuch budgeted amount to the respective SPMU at the beginning of each Fiscal Year; (b) establish and maintain, throughout the periodof the Project implementation, a State Level Steering Committee to provide guidance and approval to the SPMUs, as necessary; and(c) provide, in a timely manner, all other funds, facilities and services required for its Respective Part of the Project.

Section I.A.6 of Schedule 2. Recipient to cause NPMU to establish an operations cell, a communication and capacity building cell,and a finance and administration cell at the NPMU with professionals with the terms of reference and qualifications acceptable tothe Association, and thereafter maintain these cells, until the completion of the Project. Due Date: three months after theEffective Date

Section I.A.6: The Recipient, through NPMU and SPMUs, shall maintain specific dedicated units as per agreed staffing plan; and willengage full-time procurement specialists and finance professionals with qualification acceptable to the Bank for entire projectimplementation period.

Section I.A.7 (b): The Recipient shall ensure that the MoEF and the participating States of Gujarat, Orissa and West Bengal shallmaintain NPMU and SPMU, respectively with suitably qualified personnel with resources sufficient to carry out project managementincluding technical and fiduciary supervisions, monitoring and evaluation, and public communication to achieve the ProjectDevelopment Objectives in a timely and effective manner.

Section I.A.7 of Schedule 2. Recipient to appoint, within NPMU, an adequate number of staff with suitable qualifications andexperience acceptable to the Association and cause each of the SPMUs to appoint an adequate number of staff, with suitablequalifications and experience, acceptable to the Association. Due Date: three months after the Effective Date

Section I.A.8: The Recipient, through the NPMU and SPMUs will, within six months from effectiveness, place in position suitableexternal and internal auditors pursuant to terms of reference acceptable to the Bank, and the NPMU will submit annual audit reportsfor the entire project within six months from the close of each financial year.

Section I.A.9: Within three months from effectiveness, the Recipient, through the NPMU and the SPMUs, will establish andoperationalize computerized accounting system and maintain throughout the implementation period.

Section II.2 of Schedule 2. Recipient to furnish an Annual Action plan describing achievement of targets during the fiscal year,and the plans and physical and financial targets to be achieved during the next fiscal year. Due Date: December 31 of each year.
Section II.B.2: The Recipient, through NPMU, will submit quarterly consolidated IUFRs within 60 days from the close of the quarter
